Rami Malek, who was the first Arab-American to win a best actor Oscar, for his portrayal of Freddy Mercury in "Bohemian Rhapsody,"at the Academy Awards, 2/24/19.
(The Oscars/ABC/YouTube Screenshot)As everyone (and especially every conservative) knows, the Oscars of the last few years have been notable for their #Resistance moments.
For the most part, however, this year’s Oscars chose to let the awards speak for themselves.
The main controversy over Green Book isn’t that it glorifies racism or white supremacy (even its harshest critics recognize it does anything but).
Seth Meyers, even before Green Book actually took the top prize, did a brutal satire of “white savior” films.